{"lemma":"غَرِيمَةٍ","slug":"غَرِيمَةٍ","root":"غ.ر.م","root_slug":"غ-ر-م","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ر-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31752"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"debtor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"adversary, opponent"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb غَرِمَ (ḡarima)."},"ipa":["/ɣa.riːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31752","headword_ar":"غَرِيمٌ","root":"grm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A debtor;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o","text_ar":"خُذْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino gariymi Als~awo'i maA sabaHa","text_ar":"مِنْ غَرِيمِ السَّوْءِ مَا سَبَحَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou from the evil debtor what has become easy of attachment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaArimN","text_ar":"غَارِمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariymN","text_ar":"غَرِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon whom lies the obligation of a bloodwit"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or [it virtually signifies thus, but properly] it is a possessive epithet signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw garaAmK","text_ar":"ذُو غَرَامٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaAmapK","text_ar":"غَرَامَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tagoriymK","text_ar":"تَغْرِيمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And (sometimes, S) it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A creditor"},{"kind":"text","text":"also: (S, Msb, K:) thus having two contr. meanings; (K) Kutheiyir says, *"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaDaY kul~u *iY dayonK fawaf~aY gariymahu","text_ar":"قَضَى كُلُّ ذِى دَيْنٍ فَوَفَّى غَرِيمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"*"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEaz~apu mamoTuwlN muEan~FY gariymuhaA","text_ar":"وَعَزَّةُ مَمْطُولٌ مُعَنًّى غَرِيمُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every debtor has paid, and fully rendered to his creditor; but"},{"kind":"text","text":"as to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"'Azzeh, her creditor is put off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wearied"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) The pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariymN","text_ar":"غَرِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guramaA='u","text_ar":"غُرَمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(I Ath, Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gur~aAmN","text_ar":"غُرَّامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a strange [i. e. an anomalous] pl., (I Ath, TA;) or this is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaArimN","text_ar":"غَارِمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariymN","text_ar":"غَرِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and thus is agree able with analogy]; or it is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mugorimN","text_ar":"مُغْرِمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying “ burdened with debt. ”], formed by the rejection of the augmentative letter [of the sing]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An adversary in contention, dispute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"litigation; an antagonist; a litigant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because, by his pressing upon his adversary [like the creditor upon his debtor], he becomes one who cleaves, or clings. (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}